properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 22 at 3:30AM EST until January 22 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Miami FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, north winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts
up to 40 kt and seas 11 to 17 feet today. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northeast winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and
seas 9 to 14 feet expected tonight.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach
FL out 20 NM, Waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach FL
from 20 to 60 NM and Waters from Deerfield Beach to Ocean Reef
FL from 20 to 60 NM excluding the territorial waters of
Bahamas.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 7 PM EST this evening. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from 7 PM this evening to 7 AM EST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

A sudden onset of rough seas may cause hazardous conditions,
which may occur suddenly at jetties and inlets. These conditions
could catch boaters by surprise. Boaters should remain in port.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM EST THIS EVENING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 7 AM EST THURSDAY
